# $Id$

In no particular order ...

* Add support for loading initrd via S-records (more generic initrd support).

* Sort out exactly where $sp should point during the various stages.

* Set $sp when chain loading kernel.

* Make chain loader use LCD for error messages rather than serial.

* Add support for network booting via NFS.

* Add automatic boot via DHCP/TFTP or DHCP/NFS.

* Add boot menu using LCD.

* Don't output over the serial port unless the user requires the boot loader
  shell.

* Add support for booting from logical (extended) partitions.

* Add support for second IDE channel (NASRaQ).

-- Peter Horton, pdh@colonel-panic.org --

